{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1616bb1b-40aa-4941-a4ef-f0f57e6589e1","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws<T>` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // optional: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception object","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"15e7cf48-27f7-4790-b54a-83ff81137c9f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":247,"requestId":"CFC0:12531F:150AFEB:1868B58:69EC162B"},"id":"5c150cfb-6a14-47ad-bbc4-58343b329199","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:17:37.016Z","parentId":"be768d0f-1cda-43ae-b69a-fd4f544bad04"}
